Content:: Unaiz Farook (born 15 March 1973)[1] is a Sri Lankan politician who represents the Vanni multi-member electoral district in the Sri Lankan Parliament. He is a member of the United People's Freedom Alliance and was elected in the 2010 Parliamentary elections.[2]  This article about a politician from Northern Province, Sri Lanka is a stub.
